chunk_content: HIV testing may take place in an STI clinic, an OPD, a co-located VCT or other setting. However, if the reason for the HIV testing is the individual is either a suspect or confirmed STI case, then the test should be reported under the STI modality. i. TB: Includes persons referred for HIV testing because they have diagnosed TB (new or relapse). Refer to TB_STAT for guidelines on data collection for TB. Individuals counted under TB_STAT who already knew their status should not be reported under HTS_TST. Individuals with presumptive TB and who receive HTS should be reported under Other PITC. j. Other PITC: This includes any other provider-initiated testing and counseling that is not captured in one of the other testing modalities listed above. For reporting purposes, this includes testing of patients triaged to other clinics within the OPD that see patients for routine/chronic care (i.e., eye, dental, dermatology, diabetes, etc.).
